Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 04 of Hand MRI
When I select 'Finding' radio button
Then Finding dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Impaction and Impingement Syndrome' from the dropdown menu
Then 'Ulnocarpal impaction syndrome' radio button is enabled
And 'Radioulnar impingement' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Radioulnar impingement' radio button
Then 'Negative ulnar variance' checkbox is enabled
And 'Early phase' radio button is enabled
And 'Late phase' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Negative ulnar variance' checkbox
Then 'Secondary' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Early phase' radio button
Then 'Focal bone marrow edema proximal to the incisura ulnaris radii' radio button is enabled
And 'Chondropathy at ulnar head' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Late phase' radio button
Then 'Perifocal bone marrow edema proximal to ulnar incisura radii and at ulnar head' radio button is enabled
And 'Arrosion with perifocal sclerosis proximal to the ulnar incisura radii and at the ulnar head' radio button is enabled
